    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\n\nStarting in Bee v2.7.0, feed reads **auto-race legacy and wrapped feed formats** and return whichever resolves first \u2014 adapters no longer need to choose a feed version explicitly.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Both legacy and wrapped feed versions now race automatically on every read\n- The response header `Swarm-Feed-Resolved-Version` reports which format won\n- The `swarm-feed-legacy-resolve` query parameter was **removed** \u2014 code that still passes it will break\n- The adapter never used that query param, so we are unaffected\n\n## Related v2.7.x adapter-relevant changes\n\n- **AutoTLS / WSS**: secure WebSocket via `p2p-wss-enable` \u2014 relevant when we wire up PSS/GSOC subscriptions\n- **Redundancy validation**: `/bytes` and `/bzz` now reject invalid `Swarm-Redundancy-Level` values \u2014 we don't set it, so fine\n- **`POST /tags`** no longer requires a body \u2014 simplifies upload progress tracking\n- **`/reservestate`** now includes `reserveCapacityDoubling`\n- **v2.7.1 TopUpBatch nil-pointer fix** \u2014 prevents crashes when topping up stamps on light nodes (critical for StampManager)\n\nOur production node runs **Bee v2.7.1**.\n\n## Why it matters\n\nCodifies a forward-compatibility win (one fewer branch in read paths) and catalogs the v2.7.x changes the adapter inherits. Also a reminder to run `/health` version checks before debugging feed-read mysteries \u2014 bee-js targets Bee 2.5, and some 2.7-only behaviors (like auto-racing) are implicit.\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z"
    }
  },
